                              "content": "To achieve complete zero-knowledge privacy, all key generation and encryption procedures must occur strictly on the user's local client device before any sensitive payloads are transmitted. When a user authenticates, Ownly derives a high-entropy Master Encryption Key (MEK) from their passphrase. To prevent brute-force attacks, the client uses Argon2id (configured with 3 iterations, 64MB memory, and 4-way parallelism) or PBKDF2-SHA256 (600,000 iterations) salted with a server-supplied cryptographically secure salt.",
