                                      "id": "SNEYo",
                                      "name": "Paragraph 2",
                                      "fill": "$text-secondary",
                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "Once derived, the Master Key is ingested by an HMAC-based Expand Key Derivation Function (HKDF) to yield separate keys for local authentication and localized file encryption. Files are encrypted block-by-block using AES-256-GCM. Ownly automatically provisions a unique 96-bit Initialization Vector (IV) and a 128-bit authentication tag for each transaction. This level of zero-knowledge hygiene ensures that the system is resilient against man-in-the-middle vector risks.",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.4,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 9.5,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    },
